name: semanticscience-model
description: The Semanticscience Integrated Ontology (SIO) provides a simple, integrated ontology of types and relations for rich description of objects, processes and their attributes.

slots.name: cites
slots.description: cites is a relation to refer to by way of example, authority or proof.

slots.name: contains
slots.description: A contains B iff the spatial region occupied by A has the spatial region occupied by B as a part, and B is not part of A. [T]

slots.name: denotes
slots.description: denotes is a relation between an entity and what it is a sign or indication of, or what specifically means.

slots.name: derivesInto
slots.description: a derives to b if and only if a or some part thereof is consumed in the formation of b.

slots.name: describes
slots.description: describes is a relation between one entity and another entity that it provides a description (detailed account of).

slots.name: encodes
slots.description: A relation between two objects, in which the first object contains information that is used to produce the second object.

slots.name: existsAt
slots.description: exists at is a relation between an entity and a time measurement.

slots.name: hasAgent
slots.description: has agent is a relation between a process and an entity, where the entity is present throughout the process and is a causal participant in the process.

slots.name: hasAnnotation
slots.description: has annotation is a relation between an entity and some textual anntotation.

slots.name: hasAttribute
slots.description: has attribute is a relation that associates a entity with an attribute where an attribute is an intrinsic characteristic such as a quality, capability, disposition, function, or is an externally derived attribute determined from some descriptor (e.g. a quantity, position, label/identifier) either directly or indirectly through generalization of entities of the same type.

slots.name: hasBasis
slots.description: has basis is a relation between a realizable entity and the quality that forms the basis for it.

slots.name: hasBoundary
slots.description: has boundary is a mereological relation between a whole and boundary located at its periphery.

slots.name: hasCapability
slots.description: has capability is a relation between an entity and the capability that it bears.

slots.name: hasComponentPart
slots.description: has component part is a relation between a whole and a component part where the component is instrinsic to the whole, and loss of the part would change the kind that it is.

slots.name: hasConcretization
slots.description: A has concretization B iff A is an informational entity and B is the a quality of some material entity.

slots.name: hasCreator
slots.description: has creator is a relation between an entity and that which created it.

slots.name: hasDataItem
slots.description: has data item is a relation between a dataset and any described / referrenced entity.

slots.name: hasDirectPart
slots.description: has direct part is a relation to specify a part at a particular level of granularity

slots.name: hasDisposition
slots.description: has disposition is the relation between an entity and a disposition that it bears.

slots.name: hasEvidence
slots.description: has evidence is a relation between a proposition and something that demonstrates the truth of the assertion.

slots.name: hasFirstPart
slots.description: has first part is a proper part relation in which the part is the first of a set of linearly ordered parts resulting from the projection of the whole on a linear coordinate system.

slots.name: hasFrequency
slots.description: has frequency is a relation that specifies the occurence of an object or event

slots.name: hasFunction
slots.description: has function is the relation between an entity and a function that is ascribed to it.

slots.name: hasIdentifier
slots.description: a relation between an entity and an identifier.

slots.name: hasImplementation
slots.description: has implementation is a relation between a specification and an implementation that conforms to it.

slots.name: hasInput
slots.description: has input is a relation between a process and an entity, where the entity is present at the beginning of the process.

slots.name: hasLastPart
slots.description: has last part is a proper part relation in which the part is the last of a set of linearly ordered parts resulting from the projection of the whole on a linear coordinate system.

slots.name: hasMeasurementValue
slots.description: has measurement value is a relation between a quality/realizable and a measurement value.

slots.name: hasMember
slots.description: has member is a mereological relation between a collection and an item.

slots.name: hasOrderedPart
slots.description: has ordered part of is a proper part relation in which the part is one of a set of linearly ordered parts resulting from the projection of the whole on a linear coordinate system.

slots.name: hasOutput
slots.description: has output is a relation between an process and an entity, where the entity is present at the end of the process.

slots.name: hasParameter
slots.description: has parameter is a relation between a process and an information content entity which modulates the behaviour of some participant.

slots.name: hasPart
slots.description: has part is a transitive, reflexive and antisymmetric relation between a whole and itself or a whole and its part.

slots.name: hasParticipant
slots.description: has participant is a relation that describes the participation of the object in the (processual) subject.

slots.name: hasPhenotype
slots.description: has phenotype is a relation between an object and an observable/measurable characteristic.

slots.name: hasProduct
slots.description: has product is a relation between an process and an entity, where a new entity exists at the end of the process.

slots.name: hasProperPart
slots.description: has proper part is an antisymmetric, irreflexive (normally transitive) relation between a whole and a distinct part.

slots.name: hasProperty
slots.description: has property is a relation between an entity and the quality, capability or role that it and it alone bears.

slots.name: hasProvider
slots.description: is provided by is a relation between an entity and the entity that provides it.

slots.name: hasQuality
slots.description: has quality is a relation between an entity and the quality that it bears.

slots.name: hasRole
slots.description: has role is a relation between an entity and a role that it bears.

slots.name: hasSource
slots.description: has source is a relation between an entity and another entity from which it stems from.

slots.name: hasSubstrate
slots.description: has substrate is a relation between a process and an object where the object is destroyed by its participation in the process.

slots.name: hasTarget
slots.description: has target is a relation between a process and an entity, where the entity is present at the beginning  of the process and undergoes a change or transformation in the process.

slots.name: hasTrigger
slots.description: has trigger is a relation between a realizable and the factor that causes it to be realized.

slots.name: hasUniqueIdentifier
slots.description: has unique identifier is an inverse functional relation between an entity and an identifier that uniquely identifies it.

slots.name: hasUnit
slots.description: has unit is a relation between a quantity and the unit it is a multiple of.

slots.name: immediatelyDerivesInto
slots.description: a immediately derives into b if and only if a or some significant part thereof is consumed in the formation of b and there are no identifiable intermediate entities between a and b.

slots.name: immediatelyPrecedes
slots.description: A non-transitive temporal relation in which one process immediately precedes another process, such that there is no interval of time between the two processes.

slots.name: immediatelyTransformsInto
slots.description: A  temporal relation in which an entity mainstains identity from one state to another.

slots.name: inRelationFrom
slots.description: a in relation from b is a comparative relation in a is the object of reference in a relation with b.

slots.name: inRelationTo
slots.description: in relation to is a comparative relation to indicate that the instance of the class holding the relation exists in relation to another entity.

slots.name: isAbout
slots.description: is about is a relation between an information content entity and the entity that its primary subject.

slots.name: isAdjacentTo
slots.description: A is adjacent to B iff there is a small, but non-zero distance between A and B

slots.name: isAgentIn
slots.description: is agent in is a relation between an entity and a process, where the entity is present throughout the process, no permanent material change occurs, and is a causal participant in the process.

slots.name: isAlternateOf
slots.description: is alternate of relates two specialized instances.

slots.name: isAnnotationOf
slots.description: is annotation of is a relation between some textual entity and the entity that it annotates.

slots.name: isAttributeOf
slots.description: is attribute of is a relation that associates an attribute with an entity where an attribute is an intrinsic characteristic such as a quality, capability, disposition, function, or is an externally derived attribute determined from some descriptor (e.g. a quantity, position, label/identifier) either directly or indirectly through generalization of entities of the same type.

slots.name: isBaseFor
slots.description: is base for is a relation between a quality and the realizable entity that it is the basis for.

slots.name: isBoundaryOf
slots.description: is boundary of is a mereological relation between a boundary located at the periphery of a whole.

slots.name: isBroaderThant
slots.description: A is broader than B (t) iff for A is broader than B.

slots.name: isCapabilityOf
slots.description: is capability of is a relation between a capability and the entity that bears it.

slots.name: isCausallyRelatedFrom
slots.description: a is causally related from b iff there is a causal chain of events from b to a

slots.name: isCausallyRelatedTo
slots.description: a is causally related to b iff there is a causal chain of events from a to b

slots.name: isCausallyRelatedWith
slots.description: A transitive, symmetric, temporal relation in which one entity is causally related with another non-identical entity.

slots.name: isCitedBy
slots.description: is cited by is a relation from an object that is referred to by way of example, authority or proof.

slots.name: isComparableTo
slots.description: is comparable to is a relation between two entities that share at least one feature whose value can be compared.

slots.name: isComponentPartOf
slots.description: is component part of is a relation between a component and a whole, where the component is instrinsic to the whole, and loss of the part would change the kind that the whole is.

slots.name: isConcretizationOf
slots.description: A is concretization of B iff A is a quality of a material entity and B is an informational entity.

slots.name: isConnectedTo
slots.description: A is connected to B iff there exists a fiat, material or temporal path between A and B. [S][T]

slots.name: isContainedIn
slots.description: A is contained in B iff the spatial region occupied by A is part of the spatial region occupied by B and A is not part of B. [T]

slots.name: isCovalentlyConnectedTo
slots.description: is covalently connected to is a relation between an atom and another atom.

slots.name: isCreatorOf
slots.description: is creator of is a relation between a creator and an entity..

slots.name: isDataItemIn
slots.description: 'is data item in' is a relation between an entity that is described or referenced in a dataset.

slots.name: isDerivedFrom
slots.description: A transitive temporal relation in which one entity was materially formed from another non-identical entity.

slots.name: isDescribedBy
slots.description: is described by is a relation between one entity and another entity that provides a description (detailed account) of it.

slots.name: isDirectPartOf
slots.description: is direct part of is a relation between a specific part (at some level of granularity) and its whole.

slots.name: isDirectlyAfter
slots.description: is directly after is a relation between entities placed on a dimensional axis in which the projection of the position of the first entity is numerically greater than the projection of the position of the second entity, and the entities are adjacent to one another.

slots.name: isDirectlyBefore
slots.description: is directly before is a relation between entities placed on a dimensional axis in which the projection of the position of the first entity is numerically less than the projection of the position of the second entity, and the entities are adjacent to one another.

slots.name: isDirectlyConnectedTo
slots.description: A is directly connected to B iff there exists a path direclty between A and B.

slots.name: isDispositionOf
slots.description: is disposition of is a relation between a disposition and the entity that it is a property of.

slots.name: isDisputedBy
slots.description: has disputing evidence is a relation between a proposition and something that disputes (does not directly support) the truth of the assertion.

slots.name: isDissimilarTo
slots.description: is dissimilar to is a relation between two entities in which one is considered dissimilar to the other based on some criteria.

slots.name: isEncodedBy
slots.description: A relation between two objects, in which the first object is produced from the information contained in the second object.

slots.name: isEqualTo
slots.description: is equal to is a comparison relation between two quantities whose value are exactly the same.

slots.name: isExpressionOf
slots.description: is expression of is a relation between more concrete expression of some conceptualization.

slots.name: isFirstPartOf
slots.description: is first part of is a proper part relation in which the part is the first of a set of linearly ordered parts resulting from the projection of the whole on a linear coordinate system.

slots.name: isFrequencyOf
slots.description: is frequency of is a relation between a temporal unit and an object or event

slots.name: isFunctionOf
slots.description: is function of is a relation between a function and an entity that it is a property of.

slots.name: isGeneralizationOf
slots.description: is generalization of is a relation between a more general instance (in terms of spatial/temporal localization & other attributres) than the other.

slots.name: isGenericallyRelatedWith
slots.description: A is generically related with B iff A is an abstract entity or an information content entity and B is a information content entity or a physical entity, respectively.

slots.name: isGreaterThan
slots.description: is greater than to is a comparison relation between two quantities in which the first has a value larger than the second.

slots.name: isGreaterThanOrEqualTo
slots.description: is greater than or equal to is a comparison relation between two quantities in which the first has a value larger or equal to the second.

slots.name: isHomologousTo
slots.description: a relation between two entities which indicates their common ancestry.

slots.name: isIdenticalTo
slots.description: is identical to is a relation between two objects that are conceptually the same notwithstanding provenance or other non-intrinsic attributes.

slots.name: isIdentifierFor
slots.description: a relation between an identifier and an entity.

slots.name: isImmediatelyDerivedFrom
slots.description: A non-transitive temporal relation in which one entity is immediately derived from a non-identical entity such that there are no intermediate entities between them.

slots.name: isImmediatelyPrecededBy
slots.description: A non-transitive temporal relation in which one process is immediately preceded by another process, such that there is no interval of time between the two processes.

slots.name: isImmediatelyTransformedFrom
slots.description: A  temporal relation in which an entity mainstains identity from one state to another.

slots.name: isImplementationOf
slots.description: is implementation of is a relation between an information entity and a specification that it conforms to.

slots.name: isInequalTo
slots.description: is inequal to is a comparison relation between two quantities whose value are not the same.

slots.name: isInputIn
slots.description: is input in is a relation between an entity and a process, where the entity is present at the beginning of the process.

slots.name: isLastPartOf
slots.description: is last part of is a proper part relation in which the part is the last of a set of linearly ordered parts resulting from the projection of the whole on a linear coordinate system.

slots.name: isLesserThan
slots.description: is lesser than to is a comparison relation between two quantities in which the first has a value smaller than the second.

slots.name: isLesserThanOrEqualTo
slots.description: is greater than to is a comparison relation between two quantities in which the first has a value smaller or equal to the second.

slots.name: isLocatedIn
slots.description: A is located in B iff the spatialtemporial region occupied by A is part of the spatialtemporal region occupied by B. [T][R]

slots.name: isLocationOf
slots.description: A is location of B iff the spatialtemporal region occupied by A has the spatialtemporal region occupied by B as a part. [T][R]

slots.name: isManifestedAs
slots.description: is manifested as is a relation between an expression and its manifestations.

slots.name: isMatchTo
slots.description: A is match to B iff A and B are terms with similar (related, broad, close, exact) meanings

slots.name: isMeasurementValueOf
slots.description: is measurement value of is a relation between a value and the entity that it is a measurement of.

slots.name: isMemberOf
slots.description: is member of is a mereological relation between a item and a collection.

slots.name: isModelOf
slots.description: is model of is a relation between a model (an artifact) and the entity it purports to represent.

slots.name: isMutualCapabilityOf
slots.description: a is mutual capability of b if and only if the realization of capability  a necessarily causes the realization of capability b.

slots.name: isMutualDispositionOf
slots.description: a is mutual disposition of b if and only if the realization of the disposition  a necessarily causes the realization of the disposition b.

slots.name: isMutualRoleOf
slots.description: a is mutual role of b if and only if the realization of role  a necessarily causes the realization of role b.

slots.name: isMutuallyRelatedTo
slots.description: a is mutually related to b if and only if the realization of the relation of a necessarily causes the realization of a relation to b.

slots.name: isNarrowerThan
slots.description: A is narrower than B iff the meaning of term A is narrower in scope than the meaning of term B

slots.name: isNarrowerThant
slots.description: A is narrower than B (t) iff for A is narrower than B.

slots.name: isNumericallyComparableTo
slots.description: is numerically comparable to is a comparison relation between two quantities whose datatype value can be compared.

slots.name: isOppositeTo
slots.description: is opposite to is a relation between two entities in which one is diametrically opposed to the other.

slots.name: isOrderedPartOf
slots.description: is ordered part of is a proper part relation in which the part is one of a set of linearly ordered parts resulting from the projection of the whole on a linear coordinate system.

slots.name: isOrthologousTo
slots.description: is orthologous to is a relation between two biological entities that share a common ancestor and occur in different species.

slots.name: isOutputOf
slots.description: is output of is a relation between an entity and a process, where the entity is present at the end of the process.

slots.name: isParalogousTo
slots.description: is paralogous to is a relation between two entities which indicates their common ancestry as a result of a gene duplication.

slots.name: isParameterIn
slots.description: is parameter in is a relation between a data item and some data transformation process.

slots.name: isPartOf
slots.description: is part of is a transitive, reflexive and anti-symmetric mereological relation between a whole and itself or a part and its whole.

slots.name: isParticipantIn
slots.description: is participant in is a relation that describes the participation of the subject in the (processual) object.

slots.name: isPhenotypeOf
slots.description: is phenotype of is a relation between an observable/measurable characteristic and an object.

slots.name: isPositionallyAfter
slots.description: is positionally after is a relation between entities placed on a dimensional axis in which the projection of the position of the first entity is numerically greater than the projection of the position of the second entity.

slots.name: isPositionallyBefore
slots.description: is positionally before is a relation between entities placed on a dimensional axis in which the projection of the position of the first entity is numerically less than the projection of the position of the second entity.

slots.name: isPriorVersionOf
slots.description: A is prior version of B iff A is a variant of B and B derives from A.

slots.name: isProductOf
slots.description: is product of is a relation between an entity and a process, where the entity is present at the end  of the process as a result of a transformation in the process target.

slots.name: isProperPartOf
slots.description: is proper part of is an asymmetric, irreflexive (normally transitive) relation between a part and its distinct whole.

slots.name: isPropertyOf
slots.description: is property of is a relation betweena  quality, capability or role and the entity that it and it alone bears.

slots.name: isProviderOf
slots.description: is provider of is a relation between a source and the entity it makes available.

slots.name: isQualityOf
slots.description: is quality of is a relation between a quality and the entity that it is a property of.

slots.name: isReferencedBy
slots.description: is reference for is a relation between a document that provides information about an entity.

slots.name: isReferredToBy
slots.description: A is referred to by B iff B is an informational entity that makes reference to A.

slots.name: isRefutedBy
slots.description: has evidence is a relation between a proposition and something that refutes (is incompatible with) the truth of the assertion.

slots.name: isRelatedTo
slots.description: A is related to B iff there is some relation between A and B.
notes: 'is related to' is the top level relation in SIO

slots.name: isRepresentedBy
slots.description: is represented by: a relation between an entity and some symbol.

slots.name: isRoleOf
slots.description: is role of is a relation between a role and the entity that it is a property of.

slots.name: isSimilarTo
slots.description: is similar to is a relation between two entities that share one or more features.

slots.name: isSourceOf
slots.description: is source of is a relation between a source of information about some entity.

slots.name: isSpatiotemporallyRelatedTo
slots.description: A is spatiotemporally related to B iff A is in the spatial or temporal vicinity of B

slots.name: isSpecializationOf
slots.description: is specialization of is a relation between a more specific instance (in terms of spatial/temporal localization & other attributres) than the other.

slots.name: isSpecifiedBy
slots.description: a relation between a product and the information content entity that specifies it.

slots.name: isSubsequentVersionOf
slots.description: A is subsequent version of B iff A is a variant of B and A derives from B.

slots.name: isSupportedBy
slots.description: is supported by is a relation between a proposition and something that supports the truth of the assertion.

slots.name: isSurroundedBy
slots.description: A 'is surrounded by' B iff the A 'is contained by' B and A 'is adjacent to' B or A 'is directly connected to' B.

slots.name: isTargetIn
slots.description: is target in is a relation between an entity and a process, where the entity is present at the beginning  of the process and undergoes a change or transformation in the process.

slots.name: isTranscribedInto
slots.description: a relation between two information content entities in which one is transcribed into (an exact or similar kind) another through some process.

slots.name: isTransformedFrom
slots.description: A transitive temporal relation in which an entity mainstains identity from one state to another.

slots.name: isUniqueIdentifierFor
slots.description: is unique identifier for is a relation between an identifier and an entity that it uniquely identifies

slots.name: isUnitOf
slots.description: is unit of is a relation between a unit and a quantity that it is a multiple of.

slots.name: isVariantOf
slots.description: is variant of: a relationship indicating that two entities are different (by some measure), but either achieve the same objectives in different ways or are permutations of one another (temporal, logical or otherwise)

slots.name: isVersionOf
slots.description: is version of is a relation that holds between any two versions in which one is a subsequent or alternate version of (through a branch).

slots.name: isWeaklyInteractingWithtransitive
slots.description: is weakly interacting with is a symmetric relation between two molecular entities (or any part thereof) that are interacting through some weak force (van der waals, hydrogen bonds, electrostatic interactions)

slots.name: isXenologousTo
slots.description: a relation between two entities which indicates their common ancestry but due to horizontal gene transfer.

slots.name: measuredAt
slots.description: measured at is a relation between a measurement value and the time measurement.

slots.name: overlapsWith
slots.description: A overlaps with B iff there is some C that is part of both A and B. [S][R]

slots.name: precedes
slots.description: A transitive, temporal relation in which one process precedes (has occured earlier than) another process.

slots.name: realizes
slots.description: realizes is a relation between a process and a realizable entity (role, function, disposition).

slots.name: references
slots.description: references is a relation between one entity and the entity that it makes reference to by name, but is not described by it.

slots.name: refersTo
slots.description: refers to is a relation between one entity and the entity that it makes reference to.

slots.name: regulates
slots.description: x regulates y if and only if x is a process and y is either a process or a quality, and the progression of x exerts an effect on the frequency, rate or extent of y

slots.name: represents
slots.description: a represents b when a serves as a sign, symbol or model of b.

slots.name: satisfies
slots.description: satisfies is a relation between an entity and the specification or objective that it conforms to.

slots.name: specifies
slots.description: A relation between an information content entity and a product that it (directly/indirectly) specifies

slots.name: surrounds
slots.description: A 'surrounds' B iff the A 'contains' B and A 'is adjacent to' B or A 'is directly connected to' B.

slots.name: transformsInto
slots.description: A transitive temporal relation in which an entity mainstains identity from one state to another.

classes.name: 1DCartesianPoint
classes.description: A 1D cartesian point is a point whose position is specified along a single dimension using Cartesian coordinates.

classes.name: 1DExtentQuantity
classes.description: A quantity that extends in single dimension.

classes.name: 2DCartesianPoint
classes.description: A 2D cartesian point is a point whose position is specified along two  dimensions using Cartesian coordinates.

classes.name: 2DExtentQuantity
classes.description: A quantity that extends in two dimensions.

classes.name: 3%27SpliceSite
classes.description: The 3' splice site is the terminal region of an exon that is 3' to the intron that is to be excised.

classes.name: 3%27UntranslatedRegion
classes.description: A three prime untranslated region (3'-UTR) is the section of messenger RNA (mRNA) that immediately follows the translation termination codon.

classes.name: 3DCartesianCoordinate
classes.description: A 3D cartesian coordinate is a coordinate that is composed of an x, y and z coordinate.

classes.name: 3DCartesianPoint
classes.description: A 3D cartesian point is a point whose position is specified along three  dimensions using Cartesian coordinates.

classes.name: 3DExtentQuantity
classes.description: A quantity that extends in three dimensions.

classes.name: 3dStructureModel
classes.description: A 3D structure model is a representation of the spatial arrangement of one or more chemical entities.

classes.name: 5%27SpliceSite
classes.description: The 5' splice site is the terminal region of an exon that is 5' to the intron that is to be excised.

classes.name: 5%27UntranslatedRegion
classes.description: The five prime untranslated region (5' UTR) is a section of messenger RNA (mRNA) and the DNA that codes for it that starts at the +1 position (where transcription begins) and ends one nucleotide before the start codon (usually AUG) of the coding region.

classes.name: ACollectionOfDuplicates
classes.description: a collection of duplicates is a collection composed of items that are an exact copy of other items in the collection.

classes.name: ACollectionOfReplicates
classes.description: a collection of replicates is a collection composed of items that are a facsimile, reproduction, or copy of other items in the collection.

classes.name: ALittleQuantifier
classes.description: None

classes.name: Abnormal
classes.description: A quality that has a value that is outside normal or average.

classes.name: Aborted
classes.description: aborted is a process status in which a started process will not complete as intended.

classes.name: AbstractRole
classes.description: An abstract role is a role whose basis lies in spatial/temporal or comparative relations.

classes.name: AbstractSection
classes.description: An abstract section is a document section that provides brief summary of a document that explains the main argument(s), topic(s) or findings.

classes.name: Academic
classes.description: An academic is an individual that participates in education and scholarship.

classes.name: AcademicDepartment
classes.description: An academic department is a division of a university or school faculty devoted to a particular academic discipline.

classes.name: AcademicOrganization
classes.description: An academic organization is a lawfully recognized organization that confers diplomas, degrees and other forms of recognition of academic achievement.

classes.name: AcademicRole
classes.description: An academic role is a social role that pertains to the academic institution.

classes.name: Acid
classes.description: An acid is a molecular entity in solution capable of donating a hydron (Bronsted acid) or capable of forming a covalent bond with an electron pair (Lewis acid).

classes.name: Acid-baseReaction
classes.description: An acid-base reaction is a chemical reaction between an acid and a base.

classes.name: AcknowledgementsSection
classes.description: An acknowledgements section is a document section that identifies individuals, groups or organizations for their support in the development of the work.

classes.name: ActiniumAtom
classes.description: None

classes.name: ActionSpecification
classes.description: An action specification is a specification composed of a sequence of instructions to achieve some objective.

classes.name: Activator
classes.description: A molecular activator is a molecular regulator that realizes its disposition to conformationally change a target molecule and increase its functionality.

classes.name: ActivatorRole
classes.description: The role of a chemical entity that increases the rate of reaction.

classes.name: ActiveIngredient
classes.description: An active ingredient is a molecular entity that exhibits biological activity.

classes.name: ActiveMovement
classes.description: active movement is the process in which an object is spatially displaced using some chemical energy.

classes.name: ActiveSite
classes.description: An active site is a molecular site in which a chemical event occurs (structural transformation or conformational change).
